==English==

===Etymology===
French [[cataclysme]], from Latinized Greek [[cataclysmos]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κατακλυσμός]]''' (''kataklysmos'') "deluge, flood", from '''[[κατακλύζω]]''' (''kataklyzo'') "to dash over, flood, deluge, inundate ", from κατά (''kata'') "downwards, towards" + '''[[κλύζω]]''' (''klyzo'') "to wash off, to wash away, to dash over".

===Noun===
'''cataclysm'''
# A sudden, violent event.
# A sudden and violent change in the earth's crust.
# A great flood.

===Derived terms===
*[[cataclysmic]]

